# .mailmap — collapse all historical commit-author identities into a single
# canonical "Ankur Sinha". `git log`, `git shortlog`, and `git blame` honour
# this file when displaying author names.
#
# Note: GitHub's web UI (contributors graph, contributors list, repo
# insights) does NOT honour .mailmap — those read raw commit metadata. To
# remove non-canonical authors from GitHub's display, the commit history
# must be rewritten and force-pushed (see commit log for the cleanup pass).

